  <data name="FBE.007" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>SchStrict definition rules:
a:b, used for multiple purposes; Separate.
1. Ignore when b is empty
2. If b is null, condition a is null
3. If b is empty, the condition is a=''
4. B is! If null, condition a is not null
5. If b is in, the starting condition is a and b
6. B is! C means the condition is a= C
7. If b is&gt;=c, then the condition is a&gt;=c
8. If b is&lt;=c, then the condition is a&lt;=c
9. If b is&gt;c, then the condition is a&gt;c
10. If b is&lt;c, then the condition is a&lt;c
11. If b contains%, then the condition is a like b
12. Other conditions are a=b
SchText definition rules:
1. If the string does not contain:, it is a multi field fuzzy query defined by the interface;
2. If it is a1: b1; In the form of a2: b2, it is a custom multi field fuzzy query;</value>
